title: Full Stack Developer
location: תל אביב -יפו, TA, IL
description:
**Description**
---------------


Cybellum is a cybersecurity company specializing in keeping physical devices like cars, medical and industrial devices cyber secure.


We are recruiting a talented and highly motivated FullStack Engineer to join our Core Team.


As a FullStack developer at Cybellum, you'll be an integral part of our Core Team, responsible for crafting intuitive and visually stunning user interfaces. Collaborating closely with product management and design teams, you'll translate requirements and Figma mockups into interactive front\-end interfaces using React and TypeScript.


Leveraging your proficiency in Python to develop and maintain backend services that power our web applications. Harnessing your strong SQL skills and experience to design and optimize database schemas. Utilizing Flask and related frameworks to create RESTful APIs, ensuring smooth communication between the front\-end and back\-end components.




**Responsibilities**
--------------------


* Collaborate with product management and design teams to transform requirements and Figma mockups into visually appealing, interactive front\-end interfaces.
* Develop high\-quality, scalable, and reusable code to ensure efficient and seamless user experiences.
* Review code and provide valuable feedback to ensure code quality and maintain best practices.
* Work closely with backend developers and quality assurance teams to integrate and test front\-end components effectively.
* Contribute to the enhancement of development processes and methodologies within the team.




**Requirements**
----------------


* Demonstrated ability to make technological and architectural decisions.
* Experience interfacing with other teams to integrate various parts of the product.
* Conduct design and code reviews to ensure quality and efficiency.
* Excellent problem\-solving skills and the ability to thrive in a collaborative team environment.
* Fluent communication skills in English, both written and verbal.

**Front End Requirements:**

* Minimum 3\+ years of experience as a software engineer.
* Proficiency in Frontend Engineering using React and TypeScript.
* **Strong knowledge of RESTful APIs and integrating front\-end interfaces with back\-end systems.**
* Proven track record as a Front\-end Developer, with a focus on building complex web applications.

**Backend Requirements:**

* Proficiency in **Python** (3\+ years of commercial use).
* Proficiency in web development with **Flask and related frameworks.**
* Strong knowledge of **SQL** (Postgres preferred) and experience with ORM technologies like SqlAlchemy, DjangoORM, etc.
* Git proficiency for version control.
* Familiarity with Docker for containerization.
* Familiarity with **Kubernetes.**


Experience with clouds (AWS, Azure) (optional but beneficial).

We're seeking an experienced and proactive Senior Full Stack Engineer to join our fast\-paced team. We're looking for someone who thrives on owning features end\-to\-end, drives technical excellence, and is eager to shape the future of our product. **Requirements:**

* Team player with great communication and a passion for building great products.

If you're someone who loves solving real\-world problems, owning features end\-to\-end, and building elegant, scalable systems — we'd love to talk!

title: Senior AI Fullstack Developer

description:

This role involves developing robust, scalable software solutions, integrating cutting\-edge AI technologies such as GPT and Gemini, and using AWS as our cloud service platform. You will be expected to lead projects from concept to deployment, collaborating closely with cross\-functional teams to innovate and deliver high\-quality products.

 **About Us**



With over 17\+ years of experience, IronCircle is one of the leading global tech education, training, and service providers sending thousands of learners to new and exciting careers, serving and developing tech\-related ecosystems.



In 2018, IronCircle entered the US market via a university partnership model and have successfully partnered with colleges and universities to train the next generation of industry professionals. Unique to our program, TDX Arena is an AI\-fueled powerhouse learning platform that helps learners apply concepts learned in class to real\-world situations.



With over 50,000 cybersecurity alumni worldwide, IronCircle is highly experienced at delivering the most effective accelerated cybersecurity training and educational programs.

 **Responsibilities**


* Design, develop, and deploy full\-stack AI solutions using Python and JavaScript.
* Implement and maintain cloud\-based applications and services on AWS.
* Work with AI models like GPT and Gemini, and frameworks such as LangChain to build intelligent and efficient systems.
* Collaborate with data scientists and backend teams to integrate AI technologies into our products.
* Ensure code quality, sustainability, and scalability.
* Mentor junior developers and contribute to the team's knowledge\-sharing effort.




**Experience/ Skills Required**


* 3\+ years of experience in software development with a strong background in Python and JavaScript.
* Proven experience with AWS cloud services (EC2, S3, Lambda, etc.).
* Extensive experience working with AI models, particularly GPT and Gemini.
* Proficiency in using AI frameworks like LangChain.
* Excellent problem\-solving skills and ability to work in a team\-oriented, collaborative environment.




**Additional Experience/Skills Preferred**


* Master's degree or higher in a relevant field.
* Experience leading a development team or managing large\-scale projects.
* Experience with PHP Laravel framework for web application development.
* Familiarity with DevOps practices and tools (CI/CD pipelines, monitoring, etc.).
* Contributions to open\-source projects or a strong portfolio of relevant projects.
* Advanced certifications in AWS, AI, or machine learning technologies.




**Values**


* Passion is our driver.
* Excellence is how we deliver.
* People are our focus \- learners and employees.
* Change creates opportunity \- we embrace change.\\
* Learning never stops and neither do we.




**Your Success is our Success**



If you're a driven, collaborative person who thrives on breaking new ground and inspiring others to do the same, you’ll feel right at home here. We’re looking for someone who's passionate, high\-performer and pushes boundaries in pursuit of something bigger.



You’re a self\-starter with a “ready to make an impact on day one” mindset—confident in your ability to add real value from the start and grow with us over the long term. If that sounds like you, we think you’ll be a perfect fit.



At our core, we're more than just a company—we're a close\-knit team on a mission to change lives through the power of education. We work hard, we play hard, and we deeply value each person’s contributions toward our shared goals. We can’t wait to welcome the next game\-changer to our team. (Yes, we mean you.)

 **Equal Employer Opportunity (EEO) Statement**



We provide equal employment opportunities (EEO) to all employees and applicants for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, age, disability or genetics. In addition to federal law requirements, we comply with applicable state and local laws governing nondiscrimination in employment in every location in which the company has facilities.

 Ready to make your impact on different products, the roadmap, and most importantly \- on billions of people worldwide who experience disabilities?
